description: The X-MEN ORIGINS series continues with your favorite German mutant, Nightcrawler! Relive his early days as a trapeze artist in Germany, witness the first time he teleported and see the events that made him the hero he is today!
name: Nativity

description: Following the events of Captain America #600, Steve Rodgers' closest friends and allies may have found a way to bring back the original Captain America. Or is what they have found something more sinister? The Red Skull's greatest plan to destroy Captain America has been in motion and it's completion is almost at hand. Will Captain America be lost forever or will he be REBORN? Collecting CAPTAIN AMERICA: REBORN #1-6 and CAPTAIN AMERICA: REBORN PRELUDE digital comic.
name: HC/TPB

description:
Collected here are the first adventures of the world's greatest heroine, Wonder Woman. Originally printed in 1941, these classic tales tell the story of Diana, a young Amazon princess who leaves her home of Paradise Island to be an ambassador to the world of man. Included in this collection are the first appearances of Diana Prince, Wonder Woman's alter ego, Steve Trevor, her mother Hippolyta as well as Wonder Woman's bullet-deflecting magic bracelets, Invisible Plane and the Lasso of Truth.


The first volume contains the Wonder Woman features from the following comics:

  • All-Star Comics no. 8 (Origin story)
  • Sensation Comics no. 1 (Wonder Woman's arrival in U.S. and taking on secret identity)
  • Sensation Comics no. 2 (Defeats Dr. Poison)
  • Sensation Comics no. 3 (Uncovers a leak in U.S. military intelligence)
  • Sensation Comics no. 4 (First appearance of Baroness Paula Von Gunther)
  • Sensation Comics no. 5 (Saves a U.S. Navy ship called "The Octopus")
  • Sensation Comics no. 6 (First appearance of the Lasso of Truth, encounters The Baroness again)
  • Sensation Comics no. 7 (Defeats a plot to destroy America's milk supply)
  • Sensation Comics no. 8 (Stops a plot to exploit female workers)
  • Sensation Comics no. 9 (The original Diana Prince returns, and Wonder Woman defeats Dr. Cue)
  • Sensation Comics no. 10 (Defeats a Japanese spy named Ishti)
  • Sensation Comics no. 11 (Wonder Woman travels to Venus to save the citizens of Eros)
  • Sensation Comics no. 12 (The Baroness returns, this time in Hollywood)
  • Wonder Woman no. 1
    • Retelling of Wonder Woman's origin
    • The Japanese infiltrate the circus and kill elephants
    • The Baroness plots in a secret base beneath her jail cell
    • The Japanese plan to invade the U.S. through Mexico
name: Volume 1

description: The most skilled and noble warrior of Paradise Island, Princess Diana traveled to the world of men and became the legendary Wonder Woman. In WONDER WOMAN ARCHIVES VOL. 2, the earliest adventures of the Amazon princess are reprinted as the heroine joins the war effort against the Axis powers. Included in this classic tome are Wonder Woman's exploits as she destroys a Nazi spy ring, prevents the theft of military codes, halts a Nazi invasion of New York, thwarts a Japanese plot to infect women with a man-hating disease, exposes international spies, and battles Mars, the god of war.
name: Volume 2

description:
She's the greatest super-heroine to ever grace the comics page! Gifted with powers by the Greek Gods, Wonder Woman left her Amazon Island home to become one of the greatest champions of "Man's World." Now more of her earliest adventures are collected in WONDER WOMAN ARCHIVES Volume Three—a 240-page hardcover reprinting the Wonder Woman stories from SENSATION COMICS #18-24 and WONDER WOMAN (first series) #5-7! Written by Wonder Woman creator William Mouton Marston, with art by H.G. Peter and Frank Godwin, Volume Three also features an introduction by noted comics historian Les Daniels (Wonder Woman: The Complete History). Wonder Woman enters a prime period with this volume that features the debut of one of her most famous adversaries: the Cheetah! Also introduced is another great villain, Dr. Psycho, to bedevil our favorite Amazon. In addition to these landmarks there is the return of Mars, Lord Conquest, the Duke of Deception, and the Earl of Greed! Toss in stories of a lost race of Incas, a school bully, a trip 1000 years into the future, Fifth Columnists, yet another face-off with the Cheetah, and much more, and you have a collection of tales that depict our favorite Amazon at her Golden-Age best!

Reprints Sensation Comics #18-24 and Wonder Woman #5-7.
name: Volume 3

description:
Wonder Woman is the world’s most popular heroine, one of comics’ true iconic characters. Armed with her super strength, magic lasso, bullet-deflecting bracelets and invisible plane, she has fought evildoers for more than 60 years. Now, some of her classic 1940s adventures are collected in WONDER WOMAN ARCHIVES Volume 4, a 204-page hardcover. This volume collects SENSATION COMICS #25-32 and WONDER WOMAN #8-9, written by Wonder Woman’s creator, Dr. William Moulton Marston, with art and cover by Harry G. Peter. In these tales, the Amazon Avenger faces off against such dire threats as Queen Clea, Giganta, The Masquerader, and myriad of Axis baddies!

Reprints Sensation Comics #25-32 and Wonder Woman #8-9.
name: Volume 4

description:
The greatest super hero comic of all-time is finally here! Wolverine: Enemy of the State's team of Mark Millar (Civil War) and John Romita Jr. (World War Hulk) reunite for the best new book of the 21st century! 
Have you ever wanted to be a super hero? Dreamed of donning a mask and just heading outside to kick some ass? Well, this is the book for you! The comic that starts where other super hero books draw the line. KICK-ASS is realistic super heroes taken to the next level. Miss out and you're an idiot!
name: Kick-Ass Hardcover

description: Doom, Thor, Black Bolt, Black Panther, Ka-Zar, Namor...There are many monarchs in the Marvel Universe, but only one so powerful and so reviled that he had to be written out of history. He is THE UNSPOKEN. And his return will have dire consequences on both our world and worlds beyond. It’s a powerful storyline that will bring dishonor for one Mighty Avenger and redemption for another, a family reunion, and ties into both DARK REIGN and WAR OF KINGS. Collecting MIGHTY AVENGERS #27-31.
name: HC/TPB

description: THE GAUNTLET begins! The event that redefines Spider-Man's classic arch-enemies one by one starts with one of his deadliest – Electro! Destitute and desperate, conned out of his life's meaning and worth—Max Dillon becomes the voice of the common man against the brutal injustice of a system overloaded by greed. With Spider-Man already looking over his shoulder. Then the drama continues as one of Peter Parker's closest friends is on the brink of ruin. This looks like a job for the Amazing Spider-Sleuth...and all clues point to the sinister SANDMAN! But all of Spidey's classic villains are being reinvented as part of "THE GAUNTLET", and Sandy is no different -- so nothing is what it seems! Plus, the violent tension between Spidey and Osborn builds to a boil in THE LIST! Collecting AMAZING SPIDER-MAN #612-616, DARK REIGN: THE LIST - AMAZING SPIDER-MAN and material from WEB OF SPIDER-MAN #2.
name: Spider-Man: The Gauntlet: Electro and Sandman

volume.name: Spider-Man: The Gauntlet - Electro And Sandman

description: 40oz Comics, for the first time in one handsome collection! Hot indy artist Jim Mahfood (Clerks, Ultimate Marvel Team-Up, Grrl Scouts: Work Sucks) brings you this collection of his underground 40oz mini-comics. Previously, these four volumes have only been available at comic book shows and thru Jim's website, so lots of people have missed out on this stuff! Featuring short stories starring Mahfood's most popular characters: the Grrl Scouts, Zombie Kid, Rocket Boy, and that lovable minister of funk, Smoke Dog! All the mini-comics are printed here in their entirety, and as an added bonus, we're throwin' in 20 pages of bonus material!!! Hot damn. This collection also features pin-ups and guest art from Andi Watson, Scott Morse, Mike Huddleston, and Steve Willaredt.

name: Lucky Luke et Phil Defer

Tutti Pazzi Per il Carnevale... Anche Cocco Bill

description: Mister No sees Bat Barlington again, with whom he served in the Flying Tigers in the early forties. Bat went to live in the region bordering on Burma, Thailand and Laos, ruled by the powerful drugs barons. Mister No and Esse-Esse join him to help in the battle against the death merchants!
name: Il Ritorno delle “Tigri”

description: Three criminals, led by a certain Robertson who maintains he is Butch Cassidy’s natural son, rob a bank in Esquel, in Patagonia, and they escape on Mister No’s plane. Together with Parker, a strange journalist who is writing a book about the legendary bandit, Jerry follows their trail…
name: La Leggenda di Butch Cassidy

description: Mister No and Parker follow the bandits’ trail by visiting the places that were the scene of the end of Butch Cassidy. The police follow in hot pursuit because they think the pair are the robbers’ accomplices. In Cassidy’s old hideout the match with the three criminals comes to a head. But what is Parker’s mysterious secret?
name: Patagonia!

description: Manaus. A Columbian turns up at the house where Pedro Moraes’s wife and son live. He brings them money from Moraes, but he wants the wife to sign a receipt and threatens the son. Mister No saves the boy and follows the trail of the Columbian, the only one who can take him to Moraes. What enigma does Pedro’s disappearance hid?
name: Il Colombiano

description: Mister No has a new client, the beautiful Miss Penelope Prescott. Thanks to chance circumstances a roll of film with compromising photos of the powerful mobster Leovigildo Cesare ends up in her possession. To recover it the mobster’s men are on the hunt for Jerry and the girl!
name: Due nel Mirino

description: Haiti. During a voodoo ceremony Mister No meets Davis, a journalist from Philadelphia. His wife Eleanor has been the victim of witchcraft, which has made her into a “living corpse”. Only one person can break the curse: the little mambo girl Lucelia!
name: Gli Adoratori del Male

description: A “bokor”, i.e. a powerful voodoo witchdoctor, has kidnapped little Lucelia. And strange, indescribable presences stir during the Haitian nights… Is too late to save Lucelia and set Davis’ wife free? Maybe not. Because a powerful spirit is watching over our heroes…
name: Baron Samedi

description: Havana, Cuba. Here Mister No meets Laura, a girl he met years before during the war. She is married to Davide Ginori, a nuclear physicist. Mister No (who is also still attracted to Laura) helps them leave the island: they have to escape from the CIA men and from a “foreign power”, all of whom are interested in Ginori…
name: "Casablanca Café"

description: The “Orpheus” is a ship that has been seized by armed men. An attractive woman with eyes that are two different colours seems to be the head of the pirates. This drives Mister No to sea, where he meets a strange captain and, in the abyss, he comes across a chest of diamonds which is coveted by many…
name: Abissi

description: A biologist, his assistant and a missionary have to reach an Indio village in the Catrimani zone, but mysterious attackers want to stop them. When, thanks to Mister No, they manage to get to the place, a horrendous and disturbing scene takes place before their very eyes!
name: La Laguna Avvelenata

description: Jesus Salvador De Rio Luna, stage name “The Indio”, is a naturally talented footballer and has been purchased by the Bogotà Millionarios. Mister No, Esse-Esse and Paulo Adolfo go to Columbia to follow their friend’s sporting enterprises. But for Jesus, blackmailed by his attorney, life is not easy…
name: Il Campione
